S. Korea to Offer Up to $3,575 in Electric Car Tax Incentives

-- B y   S h i n h y e   K a n g
-- 
2011-10-12T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/s-korea-to-offer-up-to-3-575-in-electric-car-tax-incentives.html
South Korea  plans to offer tax
incentives to buyers of electric cars to boost purchases, the
Ministry of Knowledge Economy said in an e-mailed statement
today. The government will offer a tax credit of as much as 4.2
million won ($3,575) for each car starting next year, according
to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shinhye Kang at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
